    <completion-notes>
      Audit report written to `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/audit/012-pb-016-018-019.md`.
      Verdicts: PB-016 DIVERGENT-MAJOR; PB-018 DIVERGENT-MAJOR; PB-019 DIVERGENT-MAJOR.
      AC-5b: 0/3 deployed playbooks contain an ActionType 52 LookupUserMembership node — spec FR-5 claim is empirically falsified. Owner escalation flagged in report for task 015 reconcile decisions.
      Side findings (similar in spirit to task 011's NVARCHAR(10) truncation): (1) spec/task-prompt PB-code → playbook-name mapping is INVERTED for docs/emails — actual: PB-016=Emails, PB-018=Documents, PB-019=Events. (2) `sprk_configjson` storage model splits across two tables (`sprk_analysisplaybook` for header, `sprk_playbooknode` rows for graph) — reconcile must split monolithic repo JSON before redeploy. (3) PB-018 schedule diverges (deployed=hourly, repo=daily 06:00). (4) PB-019 Create Notification has runtime template-binding bug (`{{subject}}` references a field the deployed query doesn't return).
      No deployed rows mutated (read-only). Repo source-of-truth files untouched. Task 015 must reconcile based on this audit + sibling audits 013/014.
    </completion-notes>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>Follow the `jps-playbook-audit` skill. For each of PB-016 (notification-new-documents), PB-018 (notification-new-emails), and PB-019 (notification-new-events), read the deployed `sprk_configjson` from spaarkedev1 via MCP `read_query`. Compare against the canonical repo JSON at `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-new-{documents,emails,events}.json`. Confirm presence of a Node referencing ActionType 52 (`LookupUserMembership`) in each deployed config. Document any divergences (deployed vs repo) in `notes/audit/012-pb-016-018-019.md` for downstream consumption by task 015 (reconcile).</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS playbook auditor — compares deployed Dataverse data against canonical repo source-of-truth JSON.</role>

  <goal>One audit report at `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/audit/012-pb-016-018-019.md` listing — per playbook — (a) deployed-vs-repo divergence summary (or "no divergence"), (b) confirmation of ActionType 52 LookupUserMembership node presence, (c) flag for task 015 if redeploy needed.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 spec FR-5 (line 127) audits + reconciles `sprk_configjson` for the 7 existing notification playbooks. PB-016/PB-018/PB-019 are flagged in the spec as "verified to reference ActionType 52" — this task confirms that against actual deployed state. AC-5b (line 129) explicitly requires verification of the ActionType 52 node presence. The audit report drives task 015 reconciliation.</background>
