  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load all knowledge files. Read the 3 repo JSON files for PB-016, PB-018, PB-019.</step>
    <step order="2">For each of PB-016 (notification-new-documents), PB-018 (notification-new-emails), PB-019 (notification-new-events): determine the `sprk_playbookcode` from the repo JSON header.</step>
    <step order="3">MCP `read_query` for each `sprk_analysisplaybook` row by sprk_playbookcode, returning sprk_configjson + statecode.</step>
    <step order="4">For each playbook, parse deployed sprk_configjson; locate any node where ExecutorActionType / actionTypeId / equivalent = 52. Confirm at least one such node exists.</step>
    <step order="5">For each playbook, perform a semantic diff: deployed sprk_configjson vs repo sprk_configjson (node-by-node, action-code references, parameter bindings). Document divergences (or "no divergence").</step>
    <step order="6">Create directory `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/audit/` if needed. Author `012-pb-016-018-019.md` with: per-playbook section (PB-016, PB-018, PB-019); each section contains deployed state summary, repo state summary, divergence list, ActionType 52 node confirmation, "redeploy needed" flag for task 015.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to &#x2705;.</step>
    <step order="8">If deviations from plan, document in projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/.</step>
  </steps>

